<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06064070 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06064070 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  BLACK; ETHNIC; MINORITY; VIOLENCE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Members of the Zulu and Xhosa tribes fought hand-to-hand at a hostel inSoweto, leaving at least 24 dead and 15 injured.;    A senior police officersaid hundreds of armed Zulus stormed through the Meadowlands Hostel in theblack township Sunday, hacking and spearing Xhosas to death.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  ZULU AND XHOSA TRIBES CLASH IN SOWETO; 24DIE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Terrified people were cut down as they tried to flee. Others were killed intoilets or in rooms where they had been eating and sleeping, witnesses said.;   It was the worst outbreak of factional fighting in the Johannesburg regionin recent weeks. More than 1,000 people were killed in battles last year.;   Heavily armed police with armored vehicles surrounded the hostel early today,but the situation was quiet, police said. A police helicopter hovered overheadas officers piled the bodies of the dead.;    The fighting broke out when aZulu was killed, police said, although they didn't say how he died. Zulus atthe migrant workers' hostel then went on the rampage, shooting and stabbingrival Xhosas, they said.;    In another development today, police said HarryGwala of the African National Congress survived an assassination attempt whenshots were fired during a rally in Richmond in Natal Province.;    Severalshots were fired at Gwala during the rally Saturday, but the shots missed,according to family members. The attackers fled before police could apprehendanyone, they said.;    Natal Province has been the scene of bitter fightingbetween the African National Congress and the conservative Inkatha FreedomParty in recent years. Some 5,000 people have been killed in the fighting.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Johannesburg, South Africa  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  